text="Values of partial functions">Values of <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00K7.xml"
addr="jms-00K7"
title="Partial function">partial functions</fr:link></fr:title><fr:taxon>Notation</fr:taxon><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>22</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
type="local"
href="jonmsterling.xml"
addr="jonmsterling"
title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author><fr:contributor><fr:link
type="local"
href="marcelofiore.xml"
addr="marcelofiore"
title="Marcelo Fiore">Marcelo Fiore</fr:link></fr:contributor></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\mathbin {\rightharpoonup } B]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00K7.xml"
addr="jms-00K7"
title="Partial function">partial function</fr:link>. Given <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  A]]></fr:tex>, we will write <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}{\downarrow }]]></fr:tex> to mean that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is <fr:em><fr:strong>defined</fr:strong></fr:em> at <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a]]></fr:tex>, i.e. there exists some (necessarily unique) <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[b\in  B]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a\mathrel {f}b]]></fr:tex>. When <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}{\downarrow }]]></fr:tex> holds, we may write <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> to mean the unique <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[b]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a\mathrel {f}b]]></fr:tex>, which we shall refer to as the <fr:em><fr:strong>value</fr:strong></fr:em> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[b]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
