type="local"
href="jms-00K7.xml"
addr="jms-00K7"
title="Partial function">partial function</fr:link></fr:title><fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>22</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
type="local"
href="jonmsterling.xml"
addr="jonmsterling"
title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>The <fr:em><fr:strong>domain of definition</fr:strong></fr:em> of a <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00K7.xml"
addr="jms-00K7"
title="Partial function">partial function</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\mathbin {\rightharpoonup } B]]></fr:tex> is the subset <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left \{a\in  A\,\middle \vert \,f{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}{\downarrow }\right \}\mathclose {}}\subseteq  A]]></fr:tex> spanned by elements of the domain on which the partial function is <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00KA.xml"
addr="jms-00KA"
title="Values of partial functions">defined</fr:link>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
