xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>1590</fr:anchor><fr:addr
type="user">jms-00K9</fr:addr><fr:route>jms-00K9.xml</fr:route><fr:title
text="Partial functional extensionality">Partial functional extensionality</fr:title><fr:taxon>Lemma</fr:taxon><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>22</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
type="local"
href="jonmsterling.xml"
addr="jonmsterling"
title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author><fr:contributor><fr:link
type="local"
href="marcelofiore.xml"
addr="marcelofiore"
title="Marcelo Fiore">Marcelo Fiore</fr:link></fr:contributor></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f,g\colon  A\mathbin {\rightharpoonup } B]]></fr:tex> be two <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00K7.xml"
addr="jms-00K7"
title="Partial function">partial functions</fr:link>. We have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f=g]]></fr:tex> if and only if for all <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  A]]></fr:tex>, <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00KA.xml"
addr="jms-00KA"
title="Values of partial functions">defined</fr:link> at <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a]]></fr:tex> if and only if <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[g]]></fr:tex> is defined at <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a]]></fr:tex> and, moreover, the <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00KA.xml"
addr="jms-00KA"
title="Values of partial functions">value</fr:link> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> at <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a]]></fr:tex> is the same as the <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00KA.xml"
addr="jms-00KA"
title="Values of partial functions">value</fr:link> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[g]]></fr:tex> at <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a]]></fr:tex>:</fr:p><fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[  f=g  \Longleftrightarrow   \forall  a\in  A\mathpunct {.}  {\mathopen {}\left (   f{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}{\downarrow } \Leftrightarrow  g{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}{\downarrow }  \right )\mathclose {}}  \land   f{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}} = g{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}} ]]></fr:tex>
 
   
   <fr:tree
toc="false"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>1593</fr:anchor><fr:addr
type="machine">#401</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-401.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>22</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
type="local"
href="jonmsterling.xml"
addr="jonmsterling"
title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:parent>jms-00K9</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>One direction is trivial. In the other direction, we assume
  <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[    \forall  a\in  A\mathpunct {.}    {\mathopen {}\left (     f{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}{\downarrow } \Leftrightarrow  g{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}{\downarrow }    \right )\mathclose {}}    \land     f{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}} = g{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}   ]]></fr:tex>
  to deduce <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f=g]]></fr:tex>. By <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00IM.xml"
addr="jms-00IM"
title="Relational extensionality">relational extensionality</fr:link>, it suffices to show
  <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[    \forall  a\in  A\mathpunct {.}    \forall  b\in  B\mathpunct {.}    a\mathrel {f}b \Longleftrightarrow  a\mathrel {g}b.   ]]></fr:tex></fr:p>

 <fr:p>Fixing <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  A]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[b\in  B]]></fr:tex>, we assume <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a\mathrel {f} b]]></fr:tex> to prove <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a\mathrel {g}b]]></fr:tex>. By assumption, we deduce <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[g{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}{\downarrow }]]></fr:tex> from <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}{\downarrow }]]></fr:tex>, so there exists <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[b'=g{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a\mathrel {g}b']]></fr:tex>. By our other assumption, we know that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}=g{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>, so we conclude <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a\mathrel {g}b]]></fr:tex>. The other direction works the same way.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>
 
