addr="jonmsterling"
title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:parent>jms-00KE</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>A partial function <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\mathbin {\rightharpoonup } B]]></fr:tex> associates to each element <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  A]]></fr:tex> either a unique element <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}\in  B]]></fr:tex> when <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}{\downarrow }]]></fr:tex>, or it associates nothing. Therefore, we have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathord {\#}{A}]]></fr:tex> many possibilities, each followed by <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathord {\#}{B}+1]]></fr:tex> many possibilities.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>
 
