title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:parent>jms-00KH</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>A function <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A \to  B]]></fr:tex> associates to each element <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  A]]></fr:tex> a single element <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}\in  B]]></fr:tex>. Therefore, we have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\#A]]></fr:tex> possibilities, each followed by <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\#B]]></fr:tex> possibilities.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>
 
